; The TYPED method layer — pure declarations shared verbatim by server and client (native + jsoo).
; A method is ONE value (name + arg/result codecs + optional latency-compensation stub) referenced
; from both sides, so name typos / arity drift / codec drift are compile errors, not runtime 404s.
; Deliberately tiny and dependency-light (bson only): linking it into a browser bundle costs nothing,
; and adding the hundredth method stays a one-value compile. No ppx, no functors — combinator values.

(library
 (name fennec_pulse_method)
 (public_name fennec.pulse.method)
 (wrapped false)
 (libraries fennec-mongo.bson))
